1 The Senior Resident Superior Court Judge for Wake County may order disclosure of names made
2 confidential by this section after making findings that support a conclusion that disclosure is
3 necessary to a proper administration of justice.
4 For purposes of this section, a "medical professional other than a physician" means a
5 physician assistant, nurse practitioner, registered nurse, emergency medical technician, or
6 emergency medical technician-paramedic who is licensed or credentialed by the licensing board,
7 agency, or organization responsible for licensing or credentialing that profession."
8 SECTION 5. G.S. 15-191 reads as rewritten:
9 "§ 15-191. Pending sentences unaffected.
10 Nothing in G.S. 15-187, G.S. 15-187 prior to its repeal, 15-188, and 15-190 shall be
11 construed to alter in any manner the execution of the sentence of death imposed on account of
12 any crime or crimes committed before July 1, 1935."
13 SECTION 6. If any provision of this act or its application is held invalid, the
14 invalidity does not affect other provisions or applications of this act that can be given effect
15 without the invalid provisions or application and, to this end, the provisions of this act are
16 severable.
17 SECTION 7. This act is effective when it becomes law.
